&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barts Health NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant Medical Oncologist- AOS, Skin and Gynae-oncology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a full-time Consultant post in Medical Oncology with a special interest in Acute Oncology, Skin and Gynae-Oncology. This is a substantive post and has been approved by the Royal College of Physicians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be working across two main sites: St Bartholomew’s and Whipps Cross Hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job plan comprises 10 programmed activities (PAs) and an on-call commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for dynamic individuals with the appropriate skills to join a first class Cancer team providing the full range of services to the of North-East London and beyond in a progressive teaching hospital environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Karen Tipples&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Director for Skin &amp; GU Cancer (Karen.tipples@nhs.net)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Professor Tom Powles&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Divisional Director for Cancer (Thomas.powles1@nhs.net)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Goncalo Fiel&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;General Manager for Solid Oncology, Chemotherapy and Radiotherapy (Goncalo.fiel@nhs.net)&lt;/p&gt;
